title: Shenzhou VIII spacecraft assembled for launch
description: The Shenzhou VIII spacecraft is assembled with the Long-March II-F rocket at the Jiuquan Satellite Launch Center in Northwest China's Gansu province on Oct 23, 2011. The unmanned Shenzhou VIII, part of China's first spacecraft rendezvous and docking mission, was reported to be launched in early November.
cleanContent:
The Shenzhou VIII spacecraft is assembled with the Long-March II-F rocket at the Jiuquan Satellite Launch Center in Northwest China's Gansu province on Oct 23, 2011. The unmanned Shenzhou VIII, part of China's first spacecraft rendezvous and docking mission, was reported to be launched in early November.[Photo/CFP]

The Shenzhou VIII spacecraft is assembled with the Long-March II-F rocket at the Jiuquan Satellite Launch Center in Northwest China's Gansu province on Oct 23, 2011. [Photo/CFP]

The escape tower is assembled for the Shenzhou VIII spacecraft at the Jiuquan Satellite Launch Center in Northwest China's Gansu province on Oct 23, 2011. [Photo/CFP]

The roll boosters of Long-March II-F rocket are assembled at the Jiuquan Satellite Launch Center in Northwest China's Gansu province on Oct 23, 2011. [Photo/CFP]

A part of Long-March II-F rocket is lifted to assemble at the Jiuquan Satellite Launch Center in Northwest China's Gansu province on Oct 23, 2011. [Photo/CFP]
